&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;Bean Validation&lt;/code&gt;  (as we did in &lt;a href=&#34;/computer-science/mse/itmd-515/week-3/&#34;&gt;Lab 3 - Junit, JDBC and Bean Validation&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;mysql-connector-java&lt;/code&gt;  (latest non-beta version of 8)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Use appropriate scope for all your dependencies. Why are these dependencies required if we already have the javaee-api in our pom.xml?&lt;br /&gt;
 对所有依赖项使用适当的范围。如果我们在 pom.xml 中已经有了 javaee-api，为什么需要这些依赖关系？&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Make sure your group, artifact and version look like this, and that you include the build and plugins section as per &lt;a href=&#34;/computer-science/mse/itmd-515/week-3/&#34;&gt;Lab 3 - Junit, JDBC and Bean Validation&lt;/a&gt;.  &lt;strong&gt;Remember, when you use NetBeans to generate persistence related configuration or code files (such as I did with the Persistence Unit) NetBeans adds additional dependencies to your pom.xml for you.  Clean it up and make sure yours looks like this:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
